## 3. What to Build

### `lib/shared/data/canonical_json.dart`
A pure Dart utility class `CanonicalJson` with one static method: `String encode(Map<String, dynamic> data)`. Recursively sorts all map keys alphabetically before calling `jsonEncode`. Works for nested maps and lists. This utility has no dependencies and is fully unit testable without Flutter.

### `lib/shared/data/http_client_factory.dart`
Class `HttpClientFactory`. Constructor dependencies: `SigningService`, `NonceGenerator`, `PairedSystemRegistry`.
Method: `Dio forSystem(String systemId)` â€” looks up the system, throws `ArgumentError` on unknown system (CF-03), creates a `Dio` with `BaseOptions` from `system.baseUrl`, attaches `_AgentSigningInterceptor`.

Internal class `_AgentSigningInterceptor extends Interceptor`. Overrides `onRequest`. Builds the signing input, calls `signingService.sign()`, adds headers. On signing failure, calls `handler.reject(DioException(...))`.

### `lib/shared/infrastructure/fcm_message_router.dart`
Abstract class `CapabilityCommandHandler` with one method: `Future<void> handle({required String commandId, required String systemId})`.

Class `FcmMessageRouter`. Constructor dependencies: `PairedSystemRegistry`, `AuditLogService`. Method `void registerHandler(String capabilityId, CapabilityCommandHandler handler)`. Method `Future<void> route(RemoteMessage message)` â€” implements the four-check sequence described in Constraint 2.3 above.

Constant class `CapabilityId` with three string constants matching those in `Capability` value object from Phase 2.

### `lib/di/app_module.dart`
A top-level `Future<void> setupDependencies()` function. Registers in this order:
1. `SecureStorageService` â†’ `SecureStorageServiceImpl`
2. `SigningService` â†’ `AndroidKeystoreSigningService`
3. `NonceGenerator` â†’ `CryptoNonceGenerator`
4. `AuditLogService` â†’ `SqliteAuditLogService.instance`
5. `SmsParsingService` â†’ `RegexSmsParsingService`
6. `PairingRepository` â†’ `PairingRepositoryImpl` (with an unauthenticated `Dio()`)
7. `PairedSystemRegistry` â†’ `PairedSystemRegistryImpl`
8. `HttpClientFactory`
9. `FcmMessageRouter`
10. Pairing use cases and `PairingCubit`
11. `// TODO(phase-4): Register 2FA module bindings`
12. `// TODO(phase-5): Register OTP Gateway module bindings`
13. `// TODO(phase-6): Register Payment Observation module bindings`

### Update `lib/main.dart`
Add a top-level background FCM handler function (annotated `@pragma('vm:entry-point')`).
`main()` must initialize in this order:
1. `WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized()`
2. `await Firebase.initializeApp()`
3. Register background handler
4. `await SqliteAuditLogService.instance.init()`
5. `await setupDependencies()`
6. `await getIt<PairedSystemRegistry>().reload()`
7. Register foreground FCM handler: `FirebaseMessaging.onMessage.listen((msg) => getIt<FcmMessageRouter>().route(msg))`
8. `runApp(...)`

